  application, providing a Statement of Work and a detailed questionnaire
  specification. The goal was to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to
  implement any identified missing features. The agent performed a thorough code
  review, identifying several gaps, including the absence of a tiredness
  severity scale, COMISA detection, and insufficient sleep syndrome detection. A
  detailed plan was then generated and approved. Following the plan, the agent
  successfully implemented a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with associated
  safety warnings in the , ,
  , and  files. Additionally, COMISA detection
  and specific recommendations were integrated into the  and
